@import ./_tui.convo

> user
Add cursor display and positioning for the active input sprite.

Goals:
- Show the terminal cursor when an input sprite is active.
- Hide the terminal cursor when no input sprite is active.
- Position the cursor at the current input caret location.
- Add minimal input caret state to `SpriteState`.
- Keep existing text input behavior working.
- Do not implement advanced editing in this step beyond cursor placement.

Acceptance criteria:
- Active input sprites display the cursor at the end of the input value by default.
- Cursor position respects sprite layout position and scroll offsets.
- Cursor is hidden for non-input active sprites.
- Cursor is restored/hidden correctly during dispose.
- Existing input callbacks still receive the current input value.

Update notes at the end of your response
